[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test file structure**\n\nI’m pondering whether it's idiomatic to add multiple package definitions within the same test file. It seems like maybe it’s not the best practice. I feel like I need a top-level test class outside the library package, especially since the binder in org.slf4j.impl doesn’t belong to the library package. It’s in the slf4j package, and that makes me think that having test support without a top-level test could cause issues.\n\n**Evaluating logging features**\n\nI’m considering a simpler functional feature: the LoggingFilter should filter by SLF4J backend levels. Without a backend, it defaults to NOP levels, which seems unhelpful. Currently, it only compares event streams to SLF4J logger levels. Perhaps I could use SimpleLogger system properties with the SLF4J-simple dependency, but that feels like a stretch. I also think about adding tests for MDC with custom binding in the same file. I need to understand which compile dependencies to include.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07dd2814e5da01200169fd69b61d8c8192b98de3f39aa72d8e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_WnDIMGP0IAjZZoPE4tSpwdJiJxsyosO1cnJoGAwZa6IH_1C_AQBofjiimfiE_1iywvVuItTZQ2Hmi20y1O9RQ2BgU8IMDpTcVltqTXvbLwBRCrkJba8bFUfTJj3ET8TjpZJNKJ908VDqBWEAZ0S7mOCtbyEcdQkVWzfYusRTkeueLhSf-CK6GklIIChDYbPFYH2d-QJLnVstYYkNKl71W9KEa0PxX_mFMu23b3zpkON95tKYSaMa_HmVw2vZ6siwyhLOKq77_qbSP3PcfhN9xGEi27myq3e_q0Zgy26Bcs6aXeEhrTRHKwW7jLchabJ0NnwFglIRyu09ahuWG0odLJvzR25BGz9sM_K6JMx4Dq8htA3Fnzj37vmTO1ExwL1gNvf3slrnXiRKTUBIdOOHpki6QGUNNPU7GSEukyNH1m9zxQ1hTLXCOajOlLKgdEZbT-dQtEiQ7XJqZaiHVmWzlFuwEgXte3-kDD-pZISsg_Ke6zJlJnTtjLwDkzQe0Htyq0GtkTvNSHy21-M5xKxMAqGg7f0htcHeyblADeUxW88Z_hED3KQt0LAhTxAsgG7aXH5OgJnMJM3yJiZqpzqhYRtyHWxNwrlavMI-DJFlIb7XzKST_jC4CBTurg4tGwHLVGvRFAmOUqag0dMn7cLK0jKvgbNQCHbJtwJmXXVKOIEPDyy1HzOrY3999OOG-8sbz34vamHKu6nKKl1_IBjHsTAHOyKEIcirDMZyQl0uZuqX0NGty